fields.explanation:
What's wrong with it?:

The problem with a mental filter is that you ignore the things that might make you feel good if you give them a chance.
fields.question: Are you looking only at the negatives aspects of the situation?
Did you make an assumption about what someone else is thinking?
Are you making predictions or assumptions based on how you feel?
Did you make a prediction about the future?
Did you compare yourself to someone else?
Are you imagining the worst possible case?
Are you criticizing yourself or others?

fields.explanation:
What it is: Thinking about things in all or nothing terms. 
Why its a distortion: You ignore the fact that .
fields.question: Do you feel like if it's not perfect it will be a disaster?
Did you use the words "should" or "must" or make a demand?
Are you thinking about the past?
Are you ignoring or minimizing positive things about yourself or others?
What are some good qualities that you have that the other person might not share?
Can you think of some problems the other person has that you don't have to worry about?
What is the best possible scenario?  Can you think of a way that things could turn out better than you expected?
Try and think of one good thing that is true about this situation.
Think of one good thing that is true about your situation now that wasn't true in the past.
If your thought was critical, can you think of a time when the opposite of this thought was true?
Even if your prediction comes true, can you think of some good things that will still be true?
Can you think of some problems you might still have, even if this were true?
Is this conclusion really likely?  Can you think of a good result that might occur instead?
Do the facts support your conclusion?  Can you think of any evidence that supports a more positive conclusion?
Can you think of some positive things that could be true?  What is some evidence supports them?
Can you imagine a scenario where things aren't perfect, but they're still pretty good?
What might a positive interpretation of this situation be?
What would a friend tell you to make you feel better?
